@NODE MAIN "PopupMenu"

  @{b}PureBasic - PopupMenu V1.00@{ub}

    A 'popup menu' is a quick menu which appears when you click the right
    mouse button on a particular window. In PureBasic, you can attach
    one popup menu per window which allow you to do context sensitive
    menu. The nice popupmenu.library is used to achieve that, so if you
    decide to use these functions, doesn't forget to include this library
    in your final package, as it's not a 'standard' library.

  @{b}Commands summary:@{ub}

    @{" AttachPopupMenu       " LINK AttachPopupMenu}
    @{" DisablePopupMenuItem  " LINK DisablePopupMenuItem}
    @{" FreePopupMenu         " LINK FreePopupMenu}
    @{" InitPopupMenu         " LINK InitPopupMenu}
    @{" PopupMenuBar          " LINK PopupMenuBar}
    @{" PopupMenuChecked      " LINK PopupMenuChecked}
    @{" PopupMenuCheckItem    " LINK PopupMenuCheckItem}
    @{" PopupMenuCheckSubItem " LINK PopupMenuCheckSubItem}
    @{" PopupMenuEvent        " LINK PopupMenuEvent}
    @{" PopupMenuInfo         " LINK PopupMenuInfo}
    @{" PopupMenuItem         " LINK PopupMenuItem}
    @{" PopupMenuSubBar       " LINK PopupMenuSubBar}
    @{" PopupMenuSubInfo      " LINK PopupMenuSubInfo}
    @{" PopupMenuSubItem      " LINK PopupMenuSubItem}
    @{" PopupMenuSubMenuItem  " LINK PopupMenuSubMenuItem}
    @{" PopupMenuTitle        " LINK PopupMenuTitle}
    @{" WaitPopupMenuEvent    " LINK WaitPopupMenuEvent}

    @{" PopupMenu demo " LINK PureBasic:Examples/Sources/PopupMenu.pb/Main}
@ENDNODE


@NODE AttachPopupMenu

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  @{b}Result@{ub}.w = AttachPopupMenu(@{b}#Menu@{ub}.w, @{b}Window@{ub}.l)

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
  This function must be called as the last one after each menu
  building sequence, of commands like PopupMenuTitle(),
  PopupMenuItem(), PopupMenuSubItem() and so on, else the
  menu will not be completed.

  @{b}#Menu@{ub}
  The menu to attach.

  @{b}Window@{ub}
  A valid window pointer. Get it from either OpenWindow()
  or from WindowID().

  @{b}Result@{ub}
  If this is TRUE there have been one or more errors catched
  when the menu was builded, it could be possible to display
  it but don't expect it to look like it was intended, but
  if it's FALSE no error has occurred.

@ENDNODE


@NODE DisablePopupMenuItem

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  @{b}Result@{ub}.w = DisablePopupMenuItem(@{b}#Menu@{ub}.w, @{b}Item@{ub}.w, @{b}State@{ub}.w)

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
  To enable or disable any item in a popupmenu that
  could be selected.

  @{b}#Menu@{ub}
  The menu to use.

  @{b}Item@{ub}
  The item to enable or disable.

  @{b}State@{ub}
  Set this to FALSE for enable and TRUE for disable.

  @{b}Result@{ub}
  This is TRUE if the item is successfuly changed
  else it's FALSE.

@ENDNODE


@NODE FreePopupMenu

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  FreePopupMenu(@{b}#Menu@{ub}.w)

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  Use this statement to free a popupmenu.

  @{b}#Menu@{ub}
  The menu to free.

@ENDNODE


@NODE InitPopupMenu

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  @{b}Result@{ub}.l = InitPopupMenu(@{b}#Menus@{ub}.l)

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
  Call this function as the first one, as it is the init
  routine, and test the result if you want to be sure.

  @{b}#Menus@{ub}
  How many menus that is wanted.

  @{b}Result@{ub}
  If it's TRUE then all is fine but if it's instead FALSE
  then no other functions should be called.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PopupMenuBar

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  PopupMenuBar()

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  To have a nice separator bar in the popupmenu
  then call this statement.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PopupMenuChecked

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  @{b}Result@{ub}.w = PopupMenuChecked(@{b}#Menu@{ub}.w, @{b}Item@{ub}.w)

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
  To see if a checkitem have the checkmark set or not.

  @{b}#Menu@{ub}
  The menu to use.

  @{b}Item@{ub}
  The item to look out for.

  @{b}Result@{ub}
  If this is FALSE then the checkmark is not set but if it's
  instead TRUE then it is.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PopupMenuCheckItem

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  PopupMenuCheckItem(@{b}Item@{ub}.w, @{b}Text$@{ub}, @{b}ShortCut$@{ub})

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  To create a checkitem for the popupmenu then call this
  statement. The checkmark will be in false state, not set.

  @{b}Item@{ub}
  This must be a special number for each of the different
  items that is created, so when  WaitPopupMenuEvent() or
  PopupMenuEvent()  catch a popupmenu event this number is
  what they will return.

  * Se above functions for special note.

  @{b}Text$@{ub}
  The text for this checkitem.

  @{b}ShortCut$@{ub}
  This little one character string specify what the
  keyboard shortcut will be for this checkitem. If no
  shortcut will be used then supply a empty string.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PopupMenuCheckSubItem

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  PopupMenuCheckSubItem(@{b}SubItem@{ub}.w, @{b}Text$@{ub}, @{b}ShortCut$@{ub})

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  To create a subcheckitem for the popupmenu then call this
  statement. The checkmark will be in false state, not set.

  @{b}SubItem@{ub}
  This must be a special number for each of the different
  items that is created so when  WaitPopupMenuEvent() or
  PopupMenuEvent()  catch a popupmenu event this number is
  what they will return.

  * Se above functions for special note.

  @{b}Text$@{ub}
  The text for this subcheckitem.

  @{b}ShortCut$@{ub}
  This little one character string specify what the
  keyboard shortcut will be for this item.  If no
  shortcut will be used then supply a empty string.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PopupMenuEvent

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
   @{b}Result@{ub}.l = PopupMenuEvent(@{b}#Menu@{ub}.w)

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
    This function check if any event has occurred.

    It is the right one to use if the event loop should
    go on and not do the wait that WaitPoupMenuEvent()
    will do.

    @{b}#Menu@{ub}
    The popupmenu to open if RMB is pressed.

    @{b}Result@{ub}
    The event that occurred.

    * Special Note.
    It's not only the popupmenu event that will be returned,
    also any window event will be returned if any have taken
    place instead of a popupmenu event. It's a good idea to
    avoid itemnumber that is the same as window events.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PopupMenuInfo

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  PopupMenuInfo(@{b}Text$@{ub})

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  To create an infoitem use this statement. It will
  not be possible to select this item.

  If the infoitem should be complete then a separator
  bar must be the next item after this else the text
  will be black and not the shiny one.

  How a infoitem will be drawen are set with the prefs
  program that came along with the popupmenu.library.

  @{b}Text$@{ub}
  The text for this infoitem.

@ENDNODE


