@NODE PopupMenuSubMenuItem

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  PopupMenuSubMenuItem(@{b}Text$@{ub})

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  Use this statement to create a entry to a submenu
  in the popupmenu.

  All the different subitem statements will attach a
  item to this previously created submenu.

  @{b}Text$@{ub}
  The text for this submenuitem.

@ENDNODE


@NODE PopupMenuTitle

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  PopupMenuTitle(@{b}Text$@{ub})

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  To create the menutitle then use this statement. It's
  the first menu statement that must be called when a
  popupmenu is about to be builded.

  No separator bar is needed to be the next item after
  this one to have the nice and shiny text, as it have
  to be with PopupMenuInfo() and PopupMenuSubInfo().

  @{b}Text$@{ub}
  The text for the title.

@ENDNODE


@NODE WaitPopupMenuEvent

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  @{b}Result@{ub}.l = WaitPopupMenuEvent(@{b}#Menu@{ub}.w)

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
  This function check if any event has occurred.

  It is the one to use if there is no need for the
  event loop to go on.

  @{b}#Menu@{ub}
  The popupmenu to open if RMB is pressed.

  @{b}Result@{ub}
  The event that occurred.

  * Special Note.
  It's not only the popupmenu event that will be returned,
  also any window event will be returned if any have taken
  place instead of a popupmenu event. It's a good idea to
  avoid itemnumber that is the same as window events.

@ENDNODE

